<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	  Capsule runs UNSANDBOXED: there is intentionally NO `com.apple.security.app-sandbox`
	  key here, so the app can drive the `container` CLI via Process and reach the local
	  system and network freely (sandbox network entitlements would be inert and are
	  deliberately omitted). Hardened Runtime is enabled at sign time
	  (ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME); add any Hardened-Runtime exceptions
	  (e.g. com.apple.security.cs.*) here if a future dependency requires them.

	  Sparkle: the UNSANDBOXED updater needs NO extra entitlements. Sparkle's XPC services
	  (Installer/Downloader) and the com.apple.security.temporary-exception.* keys exist only
	  for the SANDBOXED case. Because Capsule is unsandboxed, the in-process updater is used and
	  this file stays empty. The Sparkle framework is built from source via SwiftPM and signed
	  with the app under the same Developer ID, so no library-validation exception is required.
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
